      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): expose estimated context budget status",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nExpose OpenClaw's pre-prompt context budget estimate when fresh provider usage is unavailable.\n\n- capture a typed, path-free `contextBudgetStatus` snapshot from the pre-prompt estimate\n- persist that snapshot on `SessionEntry`\n- expose it on gateway session rows\n- let `/status` show estimated context usage only when fresh provider usage is unavailable or absent\n- keep positive fresh `totalTokens` authoritative\n- prevent preserved-runtime heartbeat runs from replacing the main session's budget snapshot\n- clear stale `contextBudgetStatus` anywhere session reset clears runtime token/model state\n- reserve the new top-level session field from plugin session-entry slot mirroring\n\nThis is reporting-only. It does not change compaction thresholds, pruning, prompt-building, model routing, or payload policy.\n\nRefs #80594, #54996, #77992, #84490, #83177, #43009, #83526, #8635.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/status.test.ts -t \"estimated context budget\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-session-reset.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts -t \"session rows expose estimated context budget status\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-models.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Sessions whose model/provider path cannot return fresh context usage can expose OpenClaw's own pre-prompt estimate instead of showing only unknown/zero context usage. Session reset paths now clear that persisted estimate with the rest of runtime token/model state so a new session cannot show a previous session's budget snapshot.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL2 Ubuntu 24.04 durable PR worktree on signed PR head `c0f69b8dd2`, with local dependencies installed.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the verification commands listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: The focused status tests passed, proving `/status` uses the estimated context budget fallback only when fresh usage is unavailable. The reply-run reset test passed, proving session rotation clears stale runtime fields including `contextBudgetStatus` in memory and persisted store. The gateway reset regression passed, proving `sessions.reset` returns and persists a fresh entry without stale `contextBudgetStatus`. The gateway row test passed, proving the optional row field is still exposed for current snapshots.\n\nObserved result after fix: `contextBudgetStatus` remains a path-free reporting object for current session estimates, and reset boundaries clear stale snapshots before `/status` or gateway rows can expose them.\n\nWhat was not tested: Broad `pnpm check:changed`, full Vitest suite, and a live provider-backed `/status` run were not rerun locally.",
